Algorithm 3 describes our proposed method for the outlier prediction, which requires an outlier detection algorithm (line 8) to provide the outlier labels (y) (line 9) for the training examples (line 10). Notice that the outlier prediction is not limited to only using our proposed algorithm for the outlier detection (Algorithm 2) to provide the outlier labels. Our work uses our proposed method for outlier detection (Algorithm 2) to provide the outlier labels (y) and the hidden representation as additional features ({yi-PS+j-t}j=0PS\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
